data.title: Illinois Child Welfare Agency
data.meta_description: Youth Services Network develops, provides, and coordinates services to improve the physical, psychological and social well-being of youth and families by providing psychotherapy, play therapy, counseling, case management, Wraparound facilitation, tutoring, and recreation. All services are trauma-informed, strength-based and provided in the community.
data.meta_site_name: Youth Services Network | Illinois Child Welfare Agency
data.text:
Youth Services Network is licensed by the Illinois Department of Children and Family Services as a Child Welfare Agency.

Youth Services Network is funded by the City of Rockford, Family and Youth Services Bureau, FEMA, Illinois Department of Human Services, Illinois Department of Children and Family Services, Illinois State Board of Education, Rockford School District 205, United Way of the Rock River Valley, Winnebago County Community Mental Health Board, and Winnebago County.
